TideFS is licensed under the GNU General Public License version 2 only,
with the Linux-style syscall/interface exception for applications that use the
clear syscall-like public interface boundary.

The clear interface boundary includes ordinary application use through POSIX
system calls, kernel UAPI/ioctl-style interfaces, FUSE/ublk protocol entry
points, stable command-line tools, and documented wire protocols. Independent
applications that use only those boundaries are not treated as derived works
merely because they communicate with TideFS.

Code that links to TideFS internal crates, embeds TideFS implementation code,
or depends on non-public implementation interfaces is not covered by that
interface exception merely by calling into Rust APIs.

